hip: present_in_taxon NCBITaxon:9709 ! Phocidae\nrelationship: surrounds UBERON:0004087 ! vena cava\nproperty_value: function_notes \"upon stimulation of right phrenic nerve, may cause complete closure of the caval passage to the right heart\" xsd:string\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:0035846\nname: fibrous enthesis\ncomment: fibrous entheses attach directly to bone or periosteum primarily via fibrous tissue\nintersection_of: UBERON:0035845 ! enthesis\nintersection_of: composed_primarily_of UBERON:0007846 ! dense regular connective tissue\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:0035847\nname: fibrocartilage enthesis\ncomment: fibrocartilaginous entheses attach to bone through a transitional layer of fibrocartilage from the fibrous tendon tissue the sites where tendons or ligaments insert into the bone\nintersection_of: UBERON:0035845 ! enthesis\nintersection_of: composed_primarily_of UBERON:0001995 ! fibrocartilage\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:0035965\nname: wall of blood vessel\nsynonym: \"blood vessel wall\" EXACT [FMA:67473]\nsynonym: \"vascular wall\" RELATED [BTO:0004378]\nxref: BTO:0004378\nxref: EMAPA:37987 {source=\"MA:th\"}\nxref: FMA:67473\nintersection_of: UBERON:0000060 ! anatomical wall\nintersection_of: part_of UBERON:0001981 ! blood vessel\nrelationship: composed_primarily_of UBERON:0004797 ! blood vessel layer\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:0035999\nname: dopaminergic cell groups\ndef: \"Collections of neurons in the central nervous system that have been demonstrated by histochemical fluorescence to contain the neurotransmitter dopamine ( Fuxe-1970 ).\" [NeuroNames:3138]\nsynonym: \"DA cell groups\" RELATED [NeuroNames:3138]\nsynonym: \"dopaminergic cell groups\" RELATED [NeuroNames:3138]\nsynonym: \"dopaminergic nuclei\" RELATED [NeuroNames:3138]\nxref: neuronames:3138\nis_a: UBERON:0002616 ! regional part of brain\nrelationship: composed_primarily_of CL:0000700 ! dopaminergic neuron\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:0036185\nname: Sertoli cell barrier\ndef: \"The blood-testis barrier (abbreviated as BTB) is a physical barrier between the blood vessels and the seminiferous tubules of the animal testes. The barrier is formed by tight connections between the Sertoli cells, which are sustentacular cells (supporting cells) of the seminiferous tubules, and nourish the spermatogonia. The barrier prevents passage of cytotoxic agents (bodies or substances that are toxic to cells) into the seminiferous tubules.\" [Wikipedia:Blood-testis_barrier]\nsynonym: \"blood testis barrier\" RELATED [Wikipedia:Blood-testis_barrier]\nsynonym: \"blood-testes barrier\" RELATED [Wikipedia:Blood-testis_barrier]\nxref: MESH:D001814\nxref: Wikipedia:Blood-testis_barrier\nintersection_of: UBERON:0014914 ! haemolymphatic fluid-testis barrier\nintersection_of: composed_primarily_of CL:0000216 ! Sertoli cell\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:0036186\nname: fibroelastic connective tissue\nxref: FMA:83520\nintersection_of: UBERON:0011824 ! fibrous connective tissue\nintersection_of: composed_primarily_of GO:0071953 ! elastic fiber\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:1000004\nname: collection of hair on external ear\ndef: \"A collection of hairs that grows on the external ear.\" [https://github.com/obophenotype/uberon/issues/34, UBERON:EJS]\nsubset: phenotype_rcn\nsynonym: \"external ear hair\" RELATED []\nintersection_of: UBERON:0010164 ! collection of hairs\nintersection_of: part_of UBERON:0001691 ! external ear\nrelationship: composed_primarily_of UBERON:0022279 ! strand of hair on external ear\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:1500006\nname: paired fin radial bone\ndef: \"Paired fin radial element that is composed of bone tissue.\" [https://github.com/obophenotype/uberon/issues/251, OBOL:automatic]\nintersection_of: UBERON:1600006 ! paired fin radial element\nintersection_of: composed_primarily_of UBERON:0002481 ! bone tissue\nrelationship: part_of UBERON:4300013 ! paired fin radial skeleton\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:1500007\nname: mesopterygium cartilage\ndef: \"The median, elongated basal cartilage of the pectoral fin.\" [PHENOSCAPE]\ncomment: Relevant for Elasmobranchii, Holocephali and primitive Teleostomi. {xref=\"http://www.briancoad.com/dictionary/DicPics/mesopterygium.htm\"}\nintersection_of: UBERON:4300081 ! mesopterygium element\nintersection_of: composed_primarily_of UBERON:0002418 ! cartilage tissue\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:1500008\nname: pelvic fin distal radial bone\ndef: \"Pelvic fin radial that develops from the pelvic fin endoskeletal disc. Pelvic fin distal radials are paired.\" [PHENOSCAPE]\ncomment: Placeholder definition, fix me.\nis_a: UBERON:2000508 ! pelvic fin radial bone\nintersection_of: UBERON:1600008 ! pelvic fin distal radial element\nintersection_of: composed_primarily_of UBERON:0002481 ! bone tissue\nrelationship: dc-contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0001-9114-8737 ! Melissa Haendel\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:1700006\nname: paired fin radial cartilage\ndef: \"Paired fin radial element that is composed of cartilage tissue.\" [https://github.com/obophenotype/uberon/issues/251, OBOL:automatic]\nintersection_of: UBERON:1600006 ! paired fin radial element\nintersection_of: composed_primarily_of UBERON:0002418 ! cartilage tissue\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:2000226\nname: lateral ethmoid bone\ndef: \"Endochondral bone that separates the olfactory region from the orbit, extends medially to meet its fellow medially below the frontal bones and is bordered by the mesethmoid anteriorly. It may articulate with the autopalatine and infraorbital 1 laterally. The lateral ethmoid is paired.\" [ZFIN:curator]\nsynonym: \"lateral ethmoids\" EXACT OMO:0003004 [TAO:0000226]\nsynonym: \"parethmoïde\" EXACT [PSPUB:0000141]\nsynonym: \"pleurethmoïde\" EXACT [PSPUB:0000134]\nsynonym: \"éthmoïde latéral\" EXACT [PSPUB:0000164]\nxref: ZFA:0000226\nis_a: UBERON:4300111 ! lateral ethmoid element\nrelationship: composed_primarily_of UBERON:0002481 ! bone tissue\nrelationship: develops_from UBERON:0006604 ! lamina orbitonasalis\nrelationship: overlaps UBERON:0001703 ! neurocranium\nrelationship: overlaps UBERON:2001608 ! autopalatine-lateral ethmoid joint\nrelationship: overlaps UBERON:2001679 ! mesethmoid-lateral ethmoid joint\nrelationship: overlaps UBERON:2001941 ! orbitosphenoid-lateral ethmoid joint\nrelationship: overlaps UBERON:2002032 ! lateral ethmoid-frontal joint\nrelationship: part_of UBERON:0002241 ! chondrocranium\nrelationship: part_of UBERON:0003112 ! olfactory region\nproperty_value: provenance_notes \"This class was sourced from an external ontology (teleost_anatomy). Its definitions, naming conventions and relationships may need to be checked for compatibility with uberon\" xsd:string {source=\"http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/tao.owl\"}\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:2000239\nname: mesocoracoid bone\ndef: \"Endochondral bone that articulates laterally with the medial surface of the cleithrum and ventro-medially with the scapula and coracoid. Meoscoracoid bone is a small, arch-like bone that develops from the mesocoracoid cartilage. Mesocoracoid bone is paired.\" [TAO:wd]\nsynonym: \"mesocoracoideum\" RELATED [TAO:0000239]\nxref: ZFA:0000239\nintersection_of: UBERON:4300092 ! mesocoracoid element\nintersection_of: composed_primarily_of UBERON:0002481 ! bone tissue\nrelationship: develops_from UBERON:2001537 ! mesocoracoid cartilage\nproperty_value: provenance_notes \"This class was sourced from an external ontology (teleost_anatomy). Its definitions, naming conventions and relationships may need to be checked for compatibility with uberon\" xsd:string {source=\"http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/tao.owl\"}\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:2000268\nname: anal fin proximal radial bone\ndef: \"Anal fin proximal radial element that is composed of bone tissue.\" [https://github.com/obophenotype/uberon/issues/251, OBOL:automatic]\nsynonym: \"basal radial of anal fin\" EXACT [TAO:0000268]\nsynonym: \"proximal anal-fin radial\" EXACT [TAO:0000268]\nxref: ZFA:0000268\nintersection_of: UBERON:2100268 ! anal fin proximal radial element\nintersection_of: composed_primarily_of UBERON:00024